canGoIn: takeaway coffee cups (as their plastic coating can't be removed)
take away cartons as they contain a wax coating or are styrofoam
used paper towels, tissues, napkins and serviettes (as they usually have residue)
long-life cartons - as their plastic coating cannot be removed. For example, juice cartons, milk cartons, UHT, stock cartons, aseptic packaging
shredded paper (as it is light and flies up into the air at the recycling facility clogging sorting machines and creating a safety issue for staff).
canNotGoIn: Do not put anything into the general waste bin that can be recycled or put into the green waste bin, e.g.

canGoIn: cans and can lids (including pet food)
cleaning product and detergent bottles (should be empty)
canNotGoIn: takeaway coffee cups (as their plastic coating can't be removed)
take away cartons as they contain a wax coating or are styrofoam
used paper towels, tissues, napkins and serviettes (as they usually have residue)
long-life cartons - as their plastic coating cannot be removed. For example, juice cartons, milk cartons, UHT, stock cartons, aseptic packaging
shredded paper (as it is light and flies up into the air at the recycling facility clogging sorting machines and creating a safety issue for staff).

canGoIn: fruit and vegetable scraps including citrus and onion
loose tea leaves and coffee grounds.
grass clippings and weeds (free of soil)
lime green compostable caddy liners (AS 4736 and AS 5810)
small amounts of tissues, paper towel and shredded paper.
